// Snippet Manager
// CRUD operations and version history for code snippets stored as .snippet files.

Storage: basePath/{id}.snippet for current content, basePath/.history/{id}.history (JSON) for version history.
An in-memory index (Map of id -> SnippetMeta) is built at initialization.
Version history keeps the last 100 entries; older versions are dropped.

FUNCTION constructor(basePath)
  Store basePath and derive historyPath as basePath/.history/.

---

FUNCTION initialize() -> void
  Create the main and history directories.
  Scan for .snippet files, stat each one, and populate the in-memory index.

---

FUNCTION listSnippets() -> Snippet[]
  For each indexed snippet, read its content (use empty string on read error).
  Return all snippets sorted by lastModified descending.

---

FUNCTION getSnippet(id) -> Snippet | null
  Look up in index; return null if not found. Read file content and return Snippet.

---

FUNCTION saveSnippet(id, content) -> void
  CALLS: recordVersion (snippet-manager)
  Throw if id not in index or content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Write content to disk, update lastModified in index.
  Record a version history entry (failure is non-fatal).

---

FUNCTION createSnippet(name, content) -> string
  CALLS: recordVersion (snippet-manager)
  Validate name and content. Sanitize name to form id.
  Throw if id already exists or content exceeds MAX_FILE_SIZE.
  Write the file, add to index. Record an initial version history entry (failure is non-fatal).
  Return the id.

---

FUNCTION deleteSnippet(id) -> void
  Throw if id not in index. Delete the .snippet file (throw on failure).
  Delete the .history file if it exists (failure is non-fatal).
  Remove from index.

---

FUNCTION recordVersion(id, content) -> void
  Private. Load existing history JSON or start fresh.
  Append a new entry with the current timestamp and content.
  Trim history to the last 100 entries. Write the updated JSON.

---

FUNCTION getHistory(id) -> SnippetVersionEntry[]
  Throw if id not in index. IF history file does not exist, return empty array.
  Read and parse the history JSON. Throw on read/parse failure.

---

FUNCTION getVersionAtTimestamp(id, timestamp) -> string | null
  CALLS: getHistory (snippet-manager)
  Walk history entries in order, tracking the last entry at or before the target timestamp.
  Return that entry's content, or null if none qualifies.

---

FUNCTION updateIndex(id, path) -> void
  Asynchronously stat the path and upsert the index entry. Logs error on failure.

---

FUNCTION removeFromIndex(id) -> void
  Delete the id from the in-memory index without touching disk.

---

FUNCTION reset() -> void
  Clear the entire in-memory index. Caller must call initialize() to rebuild.

---

FUNCTION getIndexSize() -> number
  Return the count of currently indexed snippets.

---

FUNCTION hasSnippet(id) -> boolean
  Return true if the id exists in the index.
